  {name: "The Ritz", phone: "", email: "info@ritzpz.co.uk", url: "http://ritzpz.co.uk/", address: "Queens Street, Penzance, Cornwall", postcode: "TR18 4BJ", image: "venue/ritz_logo.png", image_alt: "Ritz community theatre, Penzance", content: "<p>The Ritz is a large community venue, serving the people of West Cornwall.                     The venue is conveniently sited just a few yards from the centre of Penzance is perfect for drawing a crowd.</p>                      <p>The hall was constructed as a 1000-seat art-deco cinema in 1936 and then converted into a Bingo Hall in 1965. Since 2009,                     The Ritz has transformed itself yet again, from the 1960\xE2\x80\x99s Bingo Hall into a sumptuous venue hosting a wide variety of events.</p>                      <p>The building radiates its 1930\xE2\x80\x99s art-deco style of linear symmetry in the generously large foyer, and main hall.                     The cinema-designed interior has given the hall phenomenal acoustics, with a tiered floor plan that allows excellent                     viewing of the stage from every angle. It can hold up to 500 people, which makes it viable for ambitious large-scale                     events such as live music gigs, birthday and wedding parties.</p>                      <p>There is also a partition arrangement to form a more intimate venue, the \xE2\x80\x9CRitz Petite\xE2\x80\x9D, by cordoning off the                     lower tier dance floor with elegant black drapes.                     Ritz Petite can hold 300 people in itself and has the bar and smaller stage incorporated within its design.</p>                      <p>View the Ritz full events list on <a href=\"http://ritzpz.co.uk/calendar/\" title=\"Ritz Penzance Events Calendar\">their website</a></p>"},
  {name: "The Acorn Theatre", phone: "01736 363545", email: "", url: "http://theacornpenzance.com/", address: "Parade Street, Penzance, Cornwall", postcode: "TR18 4BU", image: "venue/acorn_theatre_penzace.JPG", image_alt: "Acorn Arts Centre, Penzance", content: "<p>\r\n                    The Acorn, Penzance&rsquo;s theatre, is dedicated to the performing arts \xE2\x80\x93 theatre, comedy, music and dance. As both a touring venue and a performance space for local artists, it is a vibrant, creative and life-enhancing centre for all of West Cornwall.</p>\r\n                    <p>The building has two auditoria:\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>a main auditorium, which has a balcony with 53 fixed seats and a flexible stage and seating area, allowing seating for up to 150 people</li>\r\n                        <li>a smaller downstairs auditorium with movable seating (maximum capacity 80 people) and adjoining bar.</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    The Acorn Centre plays host to a wide variety of shows including Stand up, Comedy show, Shakespeare plays, live music, talks and charity events.</p>"},
  {name: "The Minack Theatre", phone: "01736 810181", email: "", url: "http://www.minack.com/", address: "Minack Theatre, on the cliffs at Porthcurno, Cornwall", postcode: "TR19 6JU", image: "venue/minack_theatre.jpg", image_alt: "Minack Open Air Theatre", content: "<p>The Minack Theatre is Cornwall's world famous open-air theatre, built into the cliff face at Porthcurno. The theatres summer season runs from May to September presenting drama, musicals and opera in this most dramatic of settings.</p>\r\n                    <p>The Minack theatre is open to visitors year round. You can explore this world famous open-air theatre created from a cliff side at Porthcurno by Rowena Cade. The sub tropical gardens are an established favorite, especially for gardeners with a taste for the exotic. The succulent plants thrive on the open cliff side providing an added dash of colour to the Minack all year round. This is also an on site cafe, allowing guests to have lunch looking out over the theatre and cliffs.                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\"Minack\" in Cornish means a rocky place and the black headed crag below the theatre has always drawn local fishermen. Until the 1930&rsquo;s they had the gorse filled gully to themselves and the cliffs echoed to the cries of gulls not actors.</p>\r\n                    <p>From 1931 until she died in 1983 the Minack Theatre was planned, built and financed by one woman - Rowena Cade.</p>\r\n                    <p>Photo from\xC2\xA0<a href=\"http://www.minack.com/\" title=\"the minack open air theatre\" target=\"_blank\">www.minack.com</a></p>"},
  {name: "Sound Nightclub", phone: "01736 331211", email: "", url: "http://www.soundpenzance.com", address: "Branwells Mill, Market Jew Street, Penzance, Cornwall", postcode: "TR18 2LQ", image: "venue/sound_night_club_penzance.jpg", image_alt: "Sound nightclub penzance", content: "<p>SOUND is the first and last nightclub in the country, situated in downtown Penzance, Cornwall.\xC2\xA0It played host to a wide variety of music styles including chart, rock, dance,hip-hop, drum and bass, dubstep and much more</p>\r\n                    <p>SOUND has had many names over the years including Club 2k, before that Club Exodus and even earlier The Venue.</p>"},
  {name: "Trereife Park and House", phone: "01736 362750", email: "", url: "http://www.trereifepark.co.uk/", address: "Trereife Park, nr Newlyn", postcode: "TR20 8TJ", image: "venue/trereife-_park_house.jpg", image_alt: "Treriefe park and country housse", content: "                    <p>Trereife House (pronounced Treave), a beautiful centuries old family owned Estate, steeped in history is now open to the public.</p>\r\n                  <p>The predominantly Queen Anne Manor House, which in parts dates back to the reign of Elizabeth 1, and the formal gardens, \xC2\xA0are set in rolling grounds, in the stunning countryside near to Newlyn &amp; Penzance.</p>\r\n                    <p>The park plays host to a number of events throughout the year including craft fairs, party in the park, art shows, food &amp; drink exhibitions and much more.                    </p>\r\n"},
  {name: "Penlee Open Air Theatre", phone: "01736 879500", email: "", url: "http://penleeparktheatre.co.uk/", address: "Penlee Park, Penzance", postcode: "TR18 4HE", image: "venue/penlee_open_air_theatre.jpg", image_alt: "Penlee Park open air theatre", content: "<p>The Open Air Theatre in\xC2\xA0<a href=\"http://www.purelypenzance.co.uk/thetown/townheritage/penleehouse.html\" title=\"penlee park open air theatre\" target=\"_blank\">Penlee Park</a>\xC2\xA0had its first season in the early 1950s. The Theatre seats around 300 people and, being situated in the middle of Penzance, it has ample parking, lending itself to an ever increasing audience. The theatre was little used until the late 1980s but since then more companies have used it each year, drawn by its sylvan setting in this peaceful park.</p>\r\n                <p>A wide range of performances take place throughout the summer season which usually runs from July to September. In previous years, these have included Circus, Choirs, Bands, Musicals and Plays ranging from Alice in Wonderland to The Taming of the Shrew.</p>\r\n                <p>The open-air theatre owes its beginning to the Cornwall Shakespeare Festival in 1948, under the auspices of Penzance Town Council.</p>\r\n                    "}
])
